I'm lucky that in England people are much more liberal surrounding topics such as this. There's rarely religious influence anymore, at least not from what I've encountered.
The day after pill does the exact same fucking thing. It's hardly a fucking child. 3 months after conception = life

No, the tissue that builds up on the walls of the uterus during pregnancy and the foetus as a whole if it is later in the pregnancy. The foetus is not dismembered, in fact most abortions occur when there's nothing but a blastocyst (ball of cells) in the uterus. Which also means 1: no foetus is 'poisoned' as the pill is often given when the pregnancy is in it's very early stages and therefore the foetus either isn't even a foetus at all or in the first stages of development. 2: the pill doesn't poison, it triggers your body to discard the foetus or whatever more naturally (basically a miscarriage) 3: the foetus isn't sentient in the sense that it can think, feel or experience anything like a further developed baby. It's brain is nowhere near developed.
Fun fact: Jesus would've died at the ripe old age of 30 or 40 something if he wasn't crucified first

The most common methods of abortion is vacuum or d&e (dilation and evacuation). D&E requires the removal of larger tissues and for the cervix to be dilated to a larger size, however these tissues are still removed by vacuum and other instruments. This does not imply that the foetus is dismembered and dissected though. I'm obviously not an expert and perhaps it happens in some cases, but it's not common.
It's insane the lengths people go to in order to misinform others for the sake of boosting their own argument or views. I wish people wouldn't believe everything they hear either.
